        <!-- Post Content -->
        <section id="bpd_content" class="bpd-post-content">
          <h2 id="section-introduction">Introduction</h2>
          <p>QR code payments have revolutionized the way businesses accept payments from customers. With MPay Network's merchant wallet, setting up QR-based payment acceptance is straightforward and can be accomplished in just a few minutes. This guide walks you through everything you need to know to get started.</p>

          <div class="bpd-callout bpd-callout-info">
            <span class="callout-icon"><i class="fa fa-info-circle" aria-hidden="true"></i></span>
            <span>QR code payments process instantly with MPay Network. Funds are available in your merchant wallet within seconds of the customer completing the payment.</span>
          </div>

          <h2 id="section-benefits">Benefits of QR Code Payments</h2>
          <p>Before diving into the technical setup, let's explore why QR code payments are becoming the preferred choice for businesses of all sizes:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Zero hardware costs</strong> — No need for expensive POS terminals or card readers. Your phone is your terminal.</li>
            <li><strong>Instant settlement</strong> — Funds appear in your wallet immediately, improving cash flow management.</li>
            <li><strong>Lower transaction fees</strong> — QR payments typically cost 0.5-1% compared to 2-3% for traditional card processing.</li>
            <li><strong>Enhanced security</strong> — Each transaction generates a unique QR code, reducing fraud risk significantly.</li>
            <li><strong>Contactless experience</strong> — Customers never need to hand over a card or touch a shared terminal.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 id="section-setup">Setting Up Your QR Payment System</h2>
          <p>Follow these steps to configure QR code payments in your MPay Network merchant wallet:</p>

          <h3 id="section-step1">Step 1: Enable QR Payments</h3>
          <p>Navigate to <code>Settings → Payment Methods → QR Code</code> in your merchant dashboard. Toggle the QR payments switch to enable this feature. You'll need to have completed your business verification before QR payments can be activated.</p>

          <pre><code>// Example: Generating a QR payment request
const paymentRequest = {
  merchantId: "MPAY-M-2025-001234",
  amount: 25.99,
  currency: "USD",
  description: "Coffee & Pastry",
  expiresIn: 300 // seconds
};

const qrCode = await mpay.generateQR(paymentRequest);
console.log(qrCode.imageUrl);
console.log(qrCode.paymentId);</code></pre>

          <h3 id="section-step2">Step 2: Customize Your QR Code</h3>
          <p>MPay Network allows you to customize the appearance of your QR codes to match your brand. You can add your business logo, change colors, and include a custom message that appears when customers scan.</p>

          <div class="bpd-callout bpd-callout-tip">
            <span class="callout-icon"><i class="fa fa-lightbulb-o" aria-hidden="true"></i></span>
            <span><strong>Pro Tip:</strong> Print your static QR code on table tents, receipts, and at the checkout counter. Customers can scan anytime without waiting for you to generate a code.</span>
          </div>

          <h3 id="section-step3">Step 3: Test Your Integration</h3>
          <p>Before going live, use the MPay sandbox environment to test your QR payment flow. Install the consumer wallet app on a second device and complete a test transaction to verify everything works correctly.</p>

          <h2 id="section-best-practices">Best Practices</h2>
          <p>To maximize the effectiveness of QR code payments in your business, consider these proven strategies:</p>
          <ol>
            <li><strong>Display prominently</strong> — Place QR codes where customers can easily see and scan them.</li>
            <li><strong>Train your staff</strong> — Ensure all team members can assist customers with the payment process.</li>
            <li><strong>Monitor transactions</strong> — Use the merchant dashboard to track payment success rates and identify any issues.</li>
            <li><strong>Offer incentives</strong> — Consider offering a small discount for QR payments to encourage adoption.</li>
          </ol>

          <h2 id="section-troubleshooting">Common Issues & Solutions</h2>
          <p>While QR payments are generally reliable, here are some common issues merchants encounter:</p>

          <blockquote>
            <strong>"Customer says the QR code won't scan"</strong> — Ensure the QR code is displayed at sufficient size (minimum 2cm × 2cm) and that there's adequate lighting. Damaged or partially obscured codes may not scan properly.
          </blockquote>

          <p>For additional troubleshooting help, check our <a href="#" onclick="load_page('merchant_troubleshooting'); event.preventDefault();">Merchant Troubleshooting Guide</a> or reach out to our support team through the <a href="#" onclick="load_page('feedback_form'); event.preventDefault();">Feedback Form</a>.</p>

          <h2 id="section-conclusion">Conclusion</h2>
          <p>QR code payments represent the future of merchant transactions — they're fast, secure, affordable, and incredibly easy to set up with MPay Network. Whether you're a small coffee shop or a large retail chain, integrating QR payments can streamline your checkout process and improve customer satisfaction.</p>
          <p>Ready to get started? Download the MPay Network Merchant Wallet and follow our <a href="#" onclick="load_page('merchant_getting_started'); event.preventDefault();">Getting Started Guide</a> to begin accepting QR payments today.</p>
        </section>

